[
    [
        {
            "type": "title",
            "content": {
                "title_content": [
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "Probability and Statistics "
                    }
                ],
                "level": 1
            },
            "bbox": [
                346,
                180,
                648,
                200
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": {
                "paragraph_content": [
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "1. There are "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "r"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "players, with player "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "_ i"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "initially having "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "n _ { i }"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "units, "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "n _ { i } > 0"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": ", "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "i ="
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "1 , \\ldots , r"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": ". At each stage, two of the players are chosen to play a game, with the winner of the game receiving 1 unit from the loser. Any player whose fortune drops to 0 is eliminated, and this continues until a single player has all "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "\\textstyle n = \\sum _ { i = 1 } ^ { r } n _ { i }"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "units, with that player designated as the winner. Note that the mechanism to choose two players at each stage is unknown. It can be either deterministic or random. Assume that the results of successive games are independent and that each game is equally likely to be won by either of its two players. "
                    }
                ]
            },
            "bbox": [
                233,
                224,
                782,
                359
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": {
                "paragraph_content": [
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "For any set of players "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "S \\subseteq \\{ 1 , \\dots , r \\}"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": ", let "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "X ( S )"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "denote the number of games involving only members of "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "S"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": ". Does "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "E ( X ( S ) )"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "depend on the player selection mechanism? If you think it doesn’t depend, calculate the expectation. If you think it depends, give two mechanisms leading to different expectations. "
                    }
                ]
            },
            "bbox": [
                251,
                364,
                782,
                441
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": {
                "paragraph_content": [
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "2. Let "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "X _ { 1 } , X _ { 2 } , \\ldots"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "be independent Bernoulli random variables satisfying "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "P ( X _ { i } ="
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "1 ) \\ : = \\ : p"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "and "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "P ( X _ { i } = - 1 ) = q = 1 - p"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "for some "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "p \\in \\mathsf { \\Gamma } ( 0 , 1 )"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": ". Let "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "S _ { n } ~ ="
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "X _ { 1 } + \\ldots + X _ { n }"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "and "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "M = \\operatorname* { s u p } _ { n \\geq 1 } ( S _ { n } / n )"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": ". "
                    }
                ]
            },
            "bbox": [
                233,
                448,
                795,
                494
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "list",
            "content": {
                "list_type": "text_list",
                "list_items": [
                    {
                        "item_type": "text",
                        "item_content": [
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "content": "(a) Calculate "
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "equation_inline",
                                "content": "P ( M = 0 )"
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "content": ". "
                            }
                        ]
                    },
                    {
                        "item_type": "text",
                        "item_content": [
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "content": "(b) Show that "
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "equation_inline",
                                "content": "P ( p - q < M \\leq 1 ) = 1"
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "content": ". For any rational number "
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "equation_inline",
                                "content": "x \\in"
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "equation_inline",
                                "content": "( p - q , 1 ]"
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "content": ", is "
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "equation_inline",
                                "content": "P ( M = x ) > 0 ^ { * }"
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "content": "? If so, prove it. If not, find a point with zero probability. "
                            }
                        ]
                    }
                ]
            },
            "bbox": [
                259,
                503,
                779,
                568
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": {
                "paragraph_content": [
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "3. Let "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "X"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "have a uniform distribution on the interval [0,1] and let "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "N _ { m , k }"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "be the digit in the "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "m"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "th place to the right of the decimal point in "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "X ^ { k }"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": ". "
                    }
                ]
            },
            "bbox": [
                233,
                577,
                781,
                608
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "list",
            "content": {
                "list_type": "text_list",
                "list_items": [
                    {
                        "item_type": "text",
                        "item_content": [
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "content": "(a) Find "
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "equation_inline",
                                "content": "\\begin{array} { r } { \\operatorname* { l i m } _ { m  \\infty } P ( N _ { m , m } = i ) } \\end{array}"
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "content": "for "
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "equation_inline",
                                "content": "i = 0 , 1 , 2 , \\ldots , 9"
                            }
                        ]
                    },
                    {
                        "item_type": "text",
                        "item_content": [
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "content": "(b) Let "
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "equation_inline",
                                "content": "k ( m )"
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "content": "be a function of "
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "equation_inline",
                                "content": "m"
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "content": ", taking values greater than 1. Find a necessary and sufficient condition on "
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "equation_inline",
                                "content": "k ( m )"
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "content": "such that "
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "equation_inline",
                                "content": "\\begin{array} { r } { \\operatorname* { l i m } _ { m  \\infty } P ( N _ { m , k ( m ) } = } \\end{array}"
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "equation_inline",
                                "content": "\\begin{array} { r } { i ) = \\frac { 1 } { 1 0 } } \\end{array}"
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "content": "for "
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "equation_inline",
                                "content": "i = 0 , 1 , 2 , \\ldots , 9"
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "content": ". "
                            }
                        ]
                    }
                ]
            },
            "bbox": [
                259,
                617,
                794,
                684
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": {
                "paragraph_content": [
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "4. Assume we have "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "n"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "observations: "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "( Y _ { i } , \\pmb { x } _ { i } ) , ~ i = 1 , . ~ . ~ . , n"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": ", where "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "Y _ { i }"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "is the random response and "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "\\pmb { x } _ { i } = ( x _ { i 1 } , \\cdots , x _ { i p } ) ^ { T }"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "is a vector of "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "p"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "fixed covariates for the "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "i"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "th observation. Denote "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "\\beta = ( \\beta _ { 1 } , \\cdots , \\beta _ { p } )"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "be a unknown "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "p"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "-length vector of regression coefficients. Let "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "\\begin{array} { r } { \\theta _ { i } = \\sum _ { j = 1 } ^ { p } x _ { i j } \\beta _ { j } , \\mu _ { i } = E ( Y _ { i } ) } \\end{array}"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "and "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "\\sigma _ { i } ^ { 2 } ="
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "V a r ( Y _ { i } )"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": ". Assume the density of "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "Y _ { i }"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "belongs to the following exponential family: "
                    }
                ]
            },
            "bbox": [
                233,
                691,
                782,
                782
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "equation_interline",
            "content": {
                "math_content": "f \\left(y _ {i}; \\theta_ {i}\\right) = \\exp \\left\\{\\theta_ {i} y _ {i} - b \\left(\\theta_ {i}\\right) \\right\\}, \\tag {1}",
                "math_type": "latex",
                "image_source": {
                    "path": "images/1ea1365080324294cf2589ea8f55788f7f1ce8538e33006325b376e90ef4c7ba.jpg"
                }
            },
            "bbox": [
                416,
                782,
                779,
                799
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": {
                "paragraph_content": [
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "where "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "b ^ { \\prime } ( \\theta _ { i } ) = \\mu _ { i } , \\ b ^ { ' \\prime } ( \\theta _ { i } ) = \\sigma _ { i } ^ { 2 }"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": ". Suppose that all "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "\\theta _ { i }"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "’s are contained in a compact subset of a space "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "\\Theta"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": ". Let "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "\\ell _ { n } ( \\beta )"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "be the log-likelihood function of the data, and let "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "\\begin{array} { r } { H _ { n } ( \\beta ) = - \\frac { \\partial ^ { 2 } \\ell _ { n } ( \\beta ) } { \\partial \\beta \\partial \\beta ^ { T } } } \\end{array}"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "∂2`n(β) "
                    }
                ]
            },
            "bbox": [
                253,
                801,
                782,
                854
            ]
        },
